<Link id="l00913" /><CodeLine lineNumber="913"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The number of bits in a SVE register is architecturally defined</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00914" /><CodeLine lineNumber="914"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to be a multiple of this value.  If &lt;M x t&gt; has this number of bits,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00915" /><CodeLine lineNumber="915"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a &lt;n x M x t&gt; vector can be stored in a SVE register without any</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00916" /><CodeLine lineNumber="916"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// redundant bits.  If &lt;M x t&gt; has this number of bits divided by P,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00917" /><CodeLine lineNumber="917"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a &lt;n x M x t&gt; vector is stored in a SVE register by placing index i</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00918" /><CodeLine lineNumber="918"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in index i&#42;P of a &lt;n x (M&#42;P) x t&gt; vector.  The other elements of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00919" /><CodeLine lineNumber="919"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &lt;n x (M&#42;P) x t&gt; vector (such as index 1) are undefined.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00920" /><CodeLine lineNumber="920" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/aarch64/#aab727392cab1f48b15483374f8251375"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">constexpr</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/aarch64/#aab727392cab1f48b15483374f8251375">SVEBitsPerBlock</a> = 128;</span></CodeLine>
